Given point, P(5, $$-$$6, 7)<br><br>and planes x + y + z = 1<br><br>and 2x $$-$$ y $$-$$ 2z = 3<br><br>Equation of planes in vector form are<br><br>$$r.(\widehat i + \widehat j + \widehat k) = 1$$<br><br>and $$r.(2\widehat i - \widehat j - 2\widehat k) = 3$$<br><br>Since, line is parallel to the given planes.<br><br>$$\therefore$$ Line is perpendicular to the vectors,<br><br>$$\widehat i + \widehat j + \widehat k$$ and $$2\widehat i - \widehat j - 2\widehat k$$<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ Line is parallel to the vector<br><br>$$(\widehat i + \widehat j + \widehat k) \times (2\widehat i - \widehat j - 2\widehat k)$$<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   {\widehat i} &amp; {\widehat j} &amp; {\widehat k}  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 1} &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i( - 2 + 1) - \widehat j( - 2 - 2) + \widehat k( - 1 - 2)$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i( - 1) - \widehat j( - 4) + \widehat k( - 3)$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i + 4\widehat j - 3\widehat k$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ Direction ratios of the line of intersection of the given plane are $$-$$1, 4, $$-$$3 or 1, $$-$$4, 3.

